result.execSummary:
The defendant Darcy Lee Jacobson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Darcy Lee Jacobson is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Darcy Lee Jacobson was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Darcy Lee Jacobson was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

records.addlTxt: Defendant Darcy Lee Jacobson in court with attorney Gary S. Cirilli.  Defendant Darcy Lee Jacobson in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 1:33 PM. State - resolved - defendant is to plead to g/nc to counts #1, #3 and #4 as alleged, #2 - previously dismissed at PH stage, joint recommendation of 60 days in FC jail - concurrent to each other, court costs only on each count. Cirilli and Jacobson agree. Jacobson pleads NC to counts #1, #3 and #4 as alleged. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her constitutional rights by entering her plea and right to JT. Court accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State - follow joint recommendation - no objections to serving the sentence in another County as she is currently serving time in Sawyer County. Cirilli - follow joint recommendation. Jacobson makes statement. Court sentences the defendant to the following: counts #1, #3 and #4 - 60 days in FC jail - concurrent to each other - huber and good time allowed - eligible for community service under 973.03(3) -  credit to be determined by counsel within the next 10 days - no objection to serving the sentence in any other County in the State of WI but it is the ultimate decision of the Sheriff(s); costs on each count - take bond posted - remainder due in 60 days/CO (consecutive to any sentence that she may be serving at the time), submit DNA sample, right to appeal, adjourned.
